(301,1,'2013-07-03 00:26:46','2013-07-03 04:26:46','As I mentioned previously, I\'m trying to do as many of my projects with Python 3 as possible going forward, which is going to involve porting a bunch of libraries to work with Python 3.3 (I\'m using 3.3 because <code>simplejson</code> doesn\'t support 3.2, and I enjoy working with JSON much more than XML). Today\'s library is the <code>python-linkedin</code> API access library, <a href=\"http://developer.linkedin.com/documents/libraries-and-tools\">mentioned by LinkedIn themselves</a> under \"More OAuth Libraries\" and <a href=\"https://github.com/ozgur/python-linkedin\">hosted on GitHub</a>.\r\n\r\nMy port to Python 3 can be found at <a href=\"https://github.com/andrewychoi/python3-linkedin\">https://github.com/andrewychoi/python3-linkedin</a>. As issues arise, please let me know!','LinkedIn API library ported to Python 3.3','','publish','open','open','','linkedin-api-library-ported-to-python-3-3','','','2013-07-03 00:26:46','2013-07-03 04:26:46','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=301',0,'post','',4),
