(341,1,'2013-07-03 16:49:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','I mentioned in a previous post that I was having trouble getting a <code>virtualenv</code> to work with Python 3, and I think I\'ve found the issue. The machine that wasn\'t installing an up-to-date version of <code>setuptools</code> (and thus <code>pip</code>) was running <code>virtualenv 1.7</code>, where the current version is <code>1.9.1</code>. Somewhere along the upgrade chain, <code>virtualenv</code> now intelligently identifies the version of <code>pip</code> that you need, and if you don\'t have it, installs it. Now my <code>virtualenv</code> is working great, and I can get back to the business of working to write an IMAP inbox cleaner for an email tool that we use at work.','Virtualenv not installing pip for Python 3.3','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-07-03 16:49:50','2013-07-03 20:49:50','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=341',0,'post','',0),
