(481,1,'2014-07-10 12:15:02','2014-07-10 16:15:02','Today I decided I needed to print something, and for the first time I had to configure a printer to use in Ubuntu. I connected my Brother HL 2140 via USB cable and tried to print, only to find that the printer hadn\'t been added (I\'ve been spoiled by Windows, I guess). I then went to System Settings -&gt; Printers -&gt; Add, and connected the Brother printer that was attached via USB. Tried printing then, and blank page after blank page kept coming out! I cancelled the print job, and realized that the printer couldn\'t handle PostScript. After messing around with a few other drivers, I found that the \"Brother HL-2140 Foomatic/hl1250\" driver worked for me. If I have to print something else out, I may try experimenting with others, but since this works for me right now, I won\'t try to fix it any further.','Printing blank pages with Brother HL 2140 and Ubuntu 14.04','','publish','open','open','','printing-blank-pages-with-brother-hl-2140-and-ubuntu-14-04','','','2014-07-10 12:15:02','2014-07-10 16:15:02','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=481',0,'post','',3),
