(501,1,'2014-07-12 14:51:04','2014-07-12 18:51:04','I ran into this error today during development:\r\n<code>\r\nImproperlyConfigured at /project/path/here/\r\nYou\'re using the staticfiles app without having set the\r\nSTATIC_ROOT setting to a filesystem path.\r\n</code>\r\nI\'m running Django 1.6 on Ubuntu 14.04. If you\'re getting this error when you include something like the following in your template code:\r\n\r\n<code>{% load compressed %}\r\n...\r\n{% compressed_css \"bootstrap\" %}</code>\r\n\r\nMake sure you\'re using parentheses, not curly braces in your glob syntax for the <code>source_filenames</code> setting:\r\n\r\nThus,\r\n<pre>\"bootstrap\": {\r\n    \"source_filenames\": {\r\n        \"libs/bootstrap/css/boostrap.min.css\",\r\n    },\r\n    \"output_filename\": \"pipeline/css/bootstrap.css\",\r\n},\r\n</pre>\r\nbecomes\r\n<pre>\"bootstrap\": {\r\n    \"source_filenames\": (\r\n        \"libs/bootstrap/css/boostrap.min.css\",\r\n    ),\r\n    \"output_filename\": \"pipeline/css/bootstrap.css\",\r\n},\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nSmall error, and it\'s tough to find. The error message isn\'t particularly helpful, either.','ImproperlyConfigured error using django-pipeline ','','publish','open','open','','improperlyconfigured-error-using-django-pipeline','','','2014-07-12 14:52:30','2014-07-12 18:52:30','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=501',0,'post','',0),
