(541,1,'2014-07-31 15:03:14','2014-07-31 19:03:14','Today I deleted a branch on a remote repo via the web interface, and was faced with the issue of my local repo not being updated for the changes. <code>git pull</code> and <code>git push</code> did nothing, unfortunately, and most of the solutions that I found online involved a <code>git push origin :branch_name</code> or its variants. When running this command, however, I got the following error message:\r\n<code>\r\n$ git push origin :branch_name\r\nerror: unable to delete \'branch_name\': remote ref does not exist\r\nerror: failed to push some refs to \'git@bitbucket.org:andrewchoi/repo_name.git\'\r\n</code>\r\nThankfully, after a good amount of Google-fu, I found the <code>git remote prune</code> command, which I ran on the remote <code>origin</code> like so:\r\n<code>\r\n$ git remote prune origin\r\n</code>\r\nwhich solved my issue.','git remote prune','','publish','open','open','','git-remote-prune','','','2014-07-31 15:03:14','2014-07-31 19:03:14','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=541',0,'post','',0),
