(561,1,'2014-08-12 11:52:33','2014-08-12 15:52:33','I was having an issue with Distraction Free mode with showing line numbers. I went to the user-specified Distraction Free settings (Preferences -&gt; Settings - More -&gt; Distraction Free - User) and tried to change the setting<code>\"line_numbers\": true</code>. However, when I went into Distraction Free, there were no line numbers. I tried restarting ST3 and even my whole computer, but to no avail. After some Googling, I found that to display line numbers, you have to change not just the <code>line_numbers</code> setting but also the <code>gutter</code> setting to be <code>true</code>. My user-specific Distraction Free settings now looks like:\r\n<pre>{\r\n    \"line_numbers\": true,\r\n    \"gutter\": true,\r\n    // \"line_numbers\": false,\r\n    // \"gutter\": false,\r\n    \"draw_centered\": true,\r\n    \"wrap_width\": 82,\r\n    \"word_wrap\": true,\r\n    \"scroll_past_end\": true,\r\n    \"rulers\": [],\r\n}\r\n</pre>','Line numbers not showing in Distraction Free on Sublime Text 3','','publish','open','open','','line-numbers-not-showing-in-distraction-free-on-sublime-text-3','','','2014-08-12 11:52:33','2014-08-12 15:52:33','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=561',0,'post','',1),
