(641,1,'2014-09-04 10:07:07','2014-09-04 14:07:07','If you\'re getting a failure along these lines:\r\n\r\n<code>\r\ncompiz crashed with SIGSEGV in ScaleScreen::getSelectedWindow()\r\n</code>\r\n\r\nit seems to be triggered by having multiple windows of the same application open, and then clicking on them in the launcher. This runs the screen spread feature, which is what is causing the crash. I found a fix here: http://speculator.diandian.com/post/2014-07-01/40062129998 but the skinny is that I ran\r\n\r\n<code>\r\ndconf reset -f /org/compiz/\r\n</code>\r\nand rebooted. According to that blog post, the instructions were found here: http://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2013/04/how-to-reset-unity-compiz-in-ubuntu-12-10-and-13-04.','Compiz crashing when clicking icon in launcher: Ubuntu 14.04','','publish','open','open','','compiz-crashing-when-clicking-icon-in-launcher-ubuntu-14-04','','','2014-09-04 10:07:07','2014-09-04 14:07:07','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=641',0,'post','',1),
(651,1,'2014-09-04 10:07:07','2014-09-04 14:07:07','If you\'re getting a failure along these lines:\r\n\r\n<code>\r\ncompiz crashed with SIGSEGV in ScaleScreen::getSelectedWindow()\r\n</code>\r\n\r\nit seems to be triggered by having multiple windows of the same application open, and then clicking on them in the launcher. This runs the screen spread feature, which is what is causing the crash. I found a fix here: http://speculator.diandian.com/post/2014-07-01/40062129998 but the skinny is that I ran\r\n\r\n<code>\r\ndconf reset -f /org/compiz/\r\n</code>\r\nand rebooted. According to that blog post, the instructions were found here: http://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2013/04/how-to-reset-unity-compiz-in-ubuntu-12-10-and-13-04.','Compiz crashing when clicking icon in launcher: Ubuntu 14.04','','inherit','open','open','','641-revision-v1','','','2014-09-04 10:07:07','2014-09-04 14:07:07','',641,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/2014/641-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
