(671,1,'2014-09-22 15:30:57','2014-09-22 19:30:57','If you\'re getting something like:\r\n\r\n<code>IntegrityError: duplicate key value violates unique constraint \"table_pkey\"\r\nDETAIL:  Key (id)=(3455) already exists.</code>\r\n\r\nand you\'ve just imported a database into an existing install, your database may not have the correct autoincrement value in place. In postgres, the following will fix the issue:\r\n\r\n<code>SELECT setval(\'yourtable_id_seq\', (SELECT MAX(id) from yourtable));</code>\r\n\r\nFrom: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9108833/postgres-autoincrement-not-updated-on-explicit-id-inserts\r\n','IntegrityError after importing database','','publish','open','open','','integrityerror-after-importing-database','','','2014-09-22 15:30:57','2014-09-22 19:30:57','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=671',0,'post','',0),
