(691,1,'2014-09-29 14:11:19','2014-09-29 18:11:19','I was having an issue using Django admin form widgets outside of the actual admin site, and found out that my call to form.media[\"js\"] needed to be in the <head> and not at the end of <body> as is normally advised. Otherwise, you get a\r\naddEvent is undefined error or something similar.','Using Django admin form widgets','','publish','open','open','','using-django-admin-form-widgets','','','2014-09-29 14:11:19','2014-09-29 18:11:19','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=691',0,'post','',0),
