(711,1,'2014-10-10 13:31:24','2014-10-10 17:31:24','Today I was working on toggling classes of elements in a d3-generated SVG, and addClass and removeClass weren\'t working. I verified that my selectors were correct, and also surrounded the block with a jQuery document-ready function, but no dice. I switched from using the jQuery addClass and removeClass methods to d3\'s classed() function, and the code magically started working!\r\n\r\nAs a further note, I imagine that the reason why this is the case is that addClass and removeClass don\'t recognize <path> elements, while the selectors still do.','Classes with d3 SVGs','','publish','open','open','','classes-with-d3-svgs','','','2014-10-10 13:31:24','2014-10-10 17:31:24','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=711',0,'post','',0),
(721,1,'2014-10-10 13:31:24','2014-10-10 17:31:24','Today I was working on toggling classes of elements in a d3-generated SVG, and addClass and removeClass weren\'t working. I verified that my selectors were correct, and also surrounded the block with a jQuery document-ready function, but no dice. I switched from using the jQuery addClass and removeClass methods to d3\'s classed() function, and the code magically started working!\r\n\r\nAs a further note, I imagine that the reason why this is the case is that addClass and removeClass don\'t recognize <path> elements, while the selectors still do.','Classes with d3 SVGs','','inherit','open','open','','711-revision-v1','','','2014-10-10 13:31:24','2014-10-10 17:31:24','',711,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/2014/711-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
