(761,1,'2015-03-23 13:44:56','2015-03-23 17:44:56','<pre>ImportError: ...lib/python2.7/site-packages/numpy/core/multiarray.so: undefined symbol: PyUnicodeUCS4_AsUnicodeEscapeString</pre>\r\nThe above error means that you\'ve got a Python interpreter compiled against UCS2 trying to run code that was compiled against UCS4. The solution I found was to recompile your lib (here NumPy) using a Python binary compiled with a\r\n<pre>--enable-unicode=ucs2</pre>\r\n.','ImportError: undefined symbol: PyUnicodeUCS4_AsUnicodeEscapeString','','publish','open','open','','importerror-undefined-symbol-pyunicodeucs4_asunicodeescapestring','','','2015-03-23 13:45:16','2015-03-23 17:45:16','',0,'http://www.andrewychoi.com/?p=761',0,'post','',0),
